quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  12,64,"He responded, ‚ÄúShould I trust you with him as I once trusted you with his brother ňĻJosephňļ? But ňĻonlyňļ Allah is the best Protector, and He is the Most Merciful of the merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  12,65,"When they opened their bags, they discovered that their money had been returned to them. They argued, ‚ÄúO our father! What more can we ask for? Here is our money, fully returned to us. Now we can buy more food for our family. We will watch over our brother, and obtain an extra camel-load of grain. That load can be easily secured.‚ÄĚ"
  12,66,"Jacob insisted, ‚ÄúI will not send him with you until you give me a solemn oath by Allah that you will certainly bring him back to me, unless you are totally overpowered.‚ÄĚ Then after they had given him their oaths, he concluded, ‚ÄúAllah is a Witness to what we have said.‚ÄĚ"
  12,67,"He then instructed ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúO my sons! Do not enter ňĻthe cityňļ all through one gate, but through separate gates.¬†I cannot help you against ňĻwhat is destined byňļ Allah in the least. It is only Allah Who decides. In Him I put my trust. And in Him let the faithful put their trust.‚ÄĚ"
  12,68,"Then when they entered as their father had instructed them, this did not help them against ňĻthe Will ofňļ Allah whatsoever. It was just a desire in Jacob‚Äôs heart which he satisfied. He was truly blessed with ňĻgreatňļ knowledge because of what We had taught him, but most people have no knowledge"
  12,69,"When they entered Joseph‚Äôs presence, he called his brother ňĻBenjaminňļ aside, and confided ňĻto himňļ, ‚ÄúI am indeed your brother ňĻJosephňļ! So do not feel distressed about what they have been doing.‚ÄĚ"